cs.DC, cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.GT, cs.CC 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper focuses on protecting distributed grid computations from cheating participants, which falls under the scope of distributed computing. 
2. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper deals with detecting cheating in grid computations, which is a security concern. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes improved cheater detection algorithms, which involves designing and analyzing algorithms. 
4. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper includes an economic analysis of cheaters in grid computations, which is related to game theory. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper discusses the complexity of the proposed algorithm and how it can tolerate collusions of lazy cheaters.
